{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:55:02.709870+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, both writing tools are failing with a **403 permission error** — the personal access token used by the MCP tools does not have write access to this repository. This is a limitation I cannot work around by retrying.\n\nHere's a summary of my work and the exact changes needed:\n\n---\n\n## Issue #5: Add Error Response Reference\n\n### What I found\n\n- **`docs/api/errors.md`** — Currently contains only a one-liner: \"Standard errors use a JSON object with `code` and `message` fields.\" It lacks structured documentation (field table, example).\n- **`docs/api/overview.md`** — Has a single-line link `See [Errors](errors.md) for standard error responses.` but no dedicated section or description of the error shape.\n\n### Proposed changes (to be committed)\n\n**`docs/api/errors.md`** — Expand with structured documentation:\n\n```markdown\n# API Errors\n\nAll API error responses follow the standard error response shape described below.\n\n## Error Response Shape\n\nEvery error response is a JSON object with the following fields:\n\n| Field     | Type   | Required | Description                                       |\n|-----------|--------|----------|---------------------------------------------------|\n| `code`    | number | yes      | Machine-readable error code identifying the type. |\n| `message` | string | yes      | Human-readable description of the error.          |\n\n### Example\n\n```json\n{\n  \"code\": 404,\n  \"message\": \"The requested resource was not found.\"\n}\n```\n```\n\n**`docs/api/overview.md`** — Add an \"Error Responses\" section with a link:\n\n```markdown\n# API Overview\n\nThis section documents the demo API reference.\n\n## Error Responses\n\nAll endpoints return errors using the [standard error response shape](errors.md), which includes a `code` and `message` field. See [Errors](errors.md) for full details and an example.\n```\n\n### Why it couldn't be committed\n\nBoth `create_or_update_file` and `push_files` returned **403: Resource not accessible by personal access token**. The token lacks write permission to the `rpnr-bench/T16_R02_C03_A01` repository. You'll need to either:\n\n1. **Grant the token write access** to the repository and retry, or\n2. **Apply the changes manually** using the content above.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 593, "prompt_tokens": 9933, "total_tokens": 10526, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 95, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9472, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007505442, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002346342, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00051591}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780865691-hc3wko3euRqbmuZUeZlL", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3dd-ef69-78d0-97b6-2c3720946551-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9933, "output_tokens": 593, "total_tokens": 10526, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9472}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 95}}}}]}}}
